metadata.name: Portraits before birth.
metadata.description:
They pose for me. They move with every blink. They know the transience of each moment. Me too.

 In a split second, the light changes. I don't mind. "You have to realize quickly, everything begins to disappear" said Cézanne.

There are parts of me in them, even my name.
But those are not my features. Or are they? It´s me? It´s everyone?

Some have faces. Others have eyes. They  are all looking.
